1606796276_16NS3rBdW9zpLmLSQoD8nLTtNVsRF.body:
Hi. If I understood correctly your problem, potentially the Yggdrasil tunnel interface was preferred for all ipv6 packets. As a matter of facts from dns you get both ipv4 and ipv6 addresses, for example:
nslookup google.com
Server:  dns.google
Name:    google.com
Addresses:  2a00:1450:400d:804::200e
                      172.217.19.110
The Yggdrasil ipv6 address is different from native ipv6 (2a00::). It's a different networks.
